reviews.text: It is a very small, very specific museum. The house it is in is absolutely beautiful and is a time capsule of sorts for the Howard family at the height of their wealth. The second floor is dedicated to boats and the river. It won't take long to go through, we did a self guided tour in a little over an hour.

If you love well preserved history then this is for you. Very knowledgeable staff and a very well preserved piece of history from the late 1800's.  I highly recommended a visit to this historic work of art. Discounts available for veterans, children and AAA members.
A great little gem with a knowledgeable staff and some really cool stuff. I'd call it the Howard Steamboat/Fireplace Museum myself. Worth the time to check it out.

It’s a two-for-one: Steamboat museum and historic home tour. 1. All you want to know, and then some, about the steamboat era; 2. Gorgeous Howard family mansion contains many original furnishings. Go! It’s terrific!

Neat little museum, very nice house with most of the original furnishings. All visits are guided, but $5 for students and kids and $7 for adults, and around a 1.5 hour tour it seems like a very reasonable charge. Better yet, it seems that most visitors go with a personal tour guide not in a group. This is a good way to spend a couple hours, and I would recommend at least doing it once just to check it out.

Good home cooking cafeteria style. Cod, roast beef chicken, pork chops are all good.
Real mashed potatoes and breaded tomatoes like mama used to make.  Many more good choices of veggies, salads and desserts. Nice variety!👍👍👍👍👍
Friendly service. Coconut cream pie was horrible. Chicken was cold. Fish was good. Rolls so-so. Disappointed with the overall meal and the price for what you were served. Go to KFC!!!!

Good Home style food. Clean but nothing fancy. Cash or credit cards. I have been here numerous times. Good prices on food, pies, salads. Special everyday. Seat yourself. Diverse crowd, business, hard hat, older couples. Just off downtown Jeffersonville Ind.

We've been going to Ann's for many years now. The type of dining, served cafeteria style, appeals to my husband and myself. The food is delicious, always served with a friendly smile and good attitude, you can get as little or as much as your wallet dictates...the prices are always reasonable. This restaurant is homey and welcoming. We need more cafeterias...they answer to the needs of people, by providing a better, healthier selection of good, home cooked meals, salads and soups and desserts. I really don't understand why cafeterias went out of style...
Great place,  food was not as hot as it should have been,  I will not be going back

The service was amazing, our waitress made sure our table was clean and we got our drinks super fast. The salad bar was really fresh. They had chicken nuggets and spaghetti for those picky eaters. The pizza bar had lots of various pizzas and it was hot. The food was excellent. They also have really good dessert that goes with the buffet.  This place is great if the whole family that wants different things. Family friendly place with great prices.

Cute joint with really friendly staff. Food was absolutely amazing and it came out quick. Really good kids menu as well and they served my daughter first which is always a plus. Definitely a place I will come back to!
Amazing pizza and the bread used for chicken parm sandwich is delicious.  I'm used to pizza from the northeast and don't like a lot of Louisville pizza places.  But this place is very good!
Pizza is consistently good. Never deviates. You know exactly what it's going to taste like every time. Would like better parking though.

I had a hankering for pizza for a week or so, I saw that all the local Bearno's were doing a fundraiser for the officer that passed away.  I stopped in about a half hour before close.  They had been extremely busy due to the public's support for the officer so they had run out of pizza, which is a good problem to have.   Unfortunately I had already paid for my pizza, they offered to exchange my pizza for sandwiches and wings, but I was craving delicious pizza.  I suggested getting a pizza tomorrow and they immediately agreed to that arrangement.  So tonight, I went in and had a nice conversation with one of the team members about our mutual love of Darth Vader, got my pizza and I could not be happier.
Had the Kentucky hot brown.  Was really good.  Service was fast and courteous.  Clean place to eat and have a drink.  Huge list of drinks and good food choices.

Staff was so friendly! My all time favorite thing (that I literally have dreams about) is their blue cheese coleslaw. The hot brown was yummy! Queso was a great starter. BBQ Boneless wings was great as a meal. We will be going back for sure!!!

Wow!
This place was a hidden gem... Was in town for work and this place was across the street... Good thing we tried because holy hell!!!
Steak was very tender, ribs were fall off the bone. Lobster Mac-n-cheese was creamy and big chunks of lobster meat throughout... Not just on top. 
All in all.... Do yourself a favor and try this place... Your tummy will thank you!!!

There was an hour wait so we chose to sit in the bar area and were immediately greeted by our server and hot yeast rolls with cinnamon butter. Server was attentive keeping our water full. Salads were fresh and entrees were fulfilling.

Had an excellent lunch here today. The service was very good and we were seated at a table with a good view of the Ohio River,  as we wanted . There was no loud music, it was not cold, and the general ambiance and appearance of the restaurant were very pleasant.  Both of us were highly pleased with our food, which was prepared just right.  We even had some dessert cake, which also was tops. The prices were also quite reasonable too. So all in all I highly recommend this restaurant!

Delicious! We shared the pasta nachos. Large portion with lots of flavor. I got the chicken bake with fettuccine and alfredo sauce. It was so good! And had plenty left over. Hubby had  the Italian Hot Brown. It was a large portion and very good. Service was very good. Cozy atmosphere. Definitely will return.
This is my comfort food. Really good Italian food. Good service. Dark, old style. Where you would go if you wanted to film a God Father scene in Louisville KY.

Nice surprise! The only reason I'm giving it four stars is because my boyfriend ordered a mushroom salad but it had next to no mushrooms. Besides that, I thought it was great. Good food and very cute on the inside.
We stopped in Friday for a cocktail and the food looked so good we decided to have dinner Saturday night.  We had crab cakes and ravioli.  The bartender and owner were awesome. Highly recommend!

Was introduced to Come Back Inn by a local family who told me about great pasta. I have to agree - the pasta that I had (cheese tortellini) and the sauce were fantastic. My table also shared a fantastic steak and gorgonzola salad. I would definitely Come Back (Inn) to try more of this delicious food.
The food was absolutely amazing. Wine selection was wonderful. And our waitress Dawn was the definition of perfection! I will be back for sure. Thanks to the staff for excellent service. You go Dawn!

Nice place we have now eaten at twice.  Good service good people and good food.  

Please sit couples out for a romantic dinner a little further away from large family crowds when you have the extra space to accommodate such. This last time there was plenty of other seats and the kiddos next to us were cute but loud and it just wasn’t what we were looking for that evening.

Found this place on Maps and figured I would give it a try—and I'm sure glad I did. Their steaks were cooked perfectly, and well seasoned. The sides were delicious and made from scratch. Will definitely come again!

Excellent service and spectacular food. The manager even refunded our appetizer do to a kitchen mix up and then when the server brought the check, he gave us a card for a free appetizer or dessert on our next visit. Kudos to Roy & Will for such great hospitality.
Excellent food and excellent service. Couldn't ask for anything more. The Hot Brown was one of the best I have ever had and the stuffed mushrooms are the best around.

I love coming to this box. My parents are in town and anytime I come to visit them I drop in here for a workout. Just FYI they’re going through a name change, they used to be CrossFit Outlook, which is still up as their sign on the building, but Google has this correctly as CrossFit Jolly Roger. Anyway they’re on the backside of a building. Tim, Becky, and Billie Sue are all very knowledgeable and super committed to safety and proper form. Anytime I asked for a clarification they already respond with not only proper technique but the underlying reasons behind it, which is most helpful for someone like me who wants to understand the what and the why. I believe they’re fairly new as a gym but that can be a very good thing. 1) You can be part of a growing community. 2) Small class sizes = more tailored coaching. 3) Individualized instruction can translate to better form, which in turn translates to quicker growth and a safer CrossFitter!

Cross Fit Jolly Roger was a great box that I plan on returning to whenever I’m in the area. The management/trainers at the facility are knowledgeable and personable. The facility is clean and well equipped. Great box for a great workout!

I started this journey over 2 years ago and I'm SO incredibly thankful that I chose to take it with CrossFit Jolly Roger! I look forward to going in every time and I always feel amazing when I leave - like I've really accomplished something. And I believe that is because of the culture and atmosphere that has been cultivated with the members and the coaches. I absolutely LOVE the coaches at CFJR. Each one brings a different style and are diligent in watching athletes to ensure proper form, which is super important to me. I don't feel like a number or means to an end. I feel like part of the family! I encourage and recommend you check out CF Jolly Roger if you're even the slightest bit interested in giving CrossFit a try.

They were great hosts when I needed to do a last minute drop in. Everyone was in good spirits and the class I was working out with was very supportive of each other and that is something that I love to see. I loved the atmosphere and I felt like I fit in as soon as I walked in there. If you’re looking to have a great community around you and motivate you, I suggest CrossFit Jolly Roger. Thank you again, guys!

I love the atmosphere here at CrossFit Jolly Roger! Everyone pushes themselves to become better everyday and no one has complaints. Our programming is top notch. You won’t find a better gym to get the best experience and be in the best shape of your life. Come see us coaches and let us show you why we are the best around!
We've been to this restaurant numerous times over the past 20 years. Tonight our chef was awesome. He changed his cooking style, we had a great time. Give him a high 5.

Are big group in celebrating freedom of just the house what's one of our lovely friends not tonight where nice couple joined this. Now we have excellent service and the next one time we got everything we ordered I'm not sure who the couple next to us made mad but they certainly did not have the same experience we did I just find it important to note that for some reason. If it had been a reverse situation this would be a different review but personally my experience was five stars had I been them. I've been getting my money back.

Japanese hibachi is as much about the experience as the food and our cook did not disappoint.  In addition to the traditional fire show, he juggled flaming batons and shot fire into the air.  The food was excellent.  The service was good.  I felt like it was money well spent.
Pretty good. It has been quite some time since we have been there. I was to say at least five years. Much better than last time. Pretty busy for a Sunday.

My brother and I celebrated our birthday's at Kobe and they made it really special. Everything was great! The service, chef, food, and of course the birthday cake. I have finally found a Hibachi place that I love in Austin.

This was my 1st time there. So very good. I got the Veggie Wrap with a Power.Slaw side. Wish they had cold green tea but water worked well. The staff there are very friendly and helpful. My husband was very happy at how great his soda was. So many places seem to weaken their sodas 
Will definitely be back. Thanks Orange Clover for the great food and service! You have a new fan.

The lunch menu had a nice variety and I was pleased to find several vegetarian items.  My grilled cheese sandwich and tomato basil soup were both tasty and  filling.  I will definitely be a return customer!
1000% love this place. Been coming here for 3 years. The service is great and the food is better. The owner is super nice and it overall has a fantastic atmosphere!

Fast service, reasonable pricing, friendly staff. A great place for dining in or outdoors. Would have gone with 5 stars, but there was a slight freshness issue with my fruit (that was handled promptly).
So delicious. So fresh! The staff is kind and efficient, and they work hard to keep the flow of the busy lunch crowd managed. Lots of food options for everyone.
I love the jaleno poppers! Arbys has excellent food but just too expensive for a quick bite to eat.
Service is slow! Food is decent! Love the sliders.
I do not think they have ever got my food wrong or ever been bad. And always seems clean. I Recommend them

Roast beef sandwiches aren't all they serve anymore. They also have gyros which are awesome. They will ask if you want Greek, but what they mean to ask is if you want lamb. 

But apparently Americans dont like to eat baby sheep and instead prefer to eat Greeks. I dont get it, but hey, it's probably a market research thing.

They really need to serve schwarma and Poutine.  

Delicious food though, and they have a coke freestyle machine.
It was ok.    Food was good and right.  Service was good bit wish it was a couple minutes faster

While the view is great, our waitress did her utmost while trying to cover too many tables, and our wait to be seated was less than expected on a Friday night - the food was kind of unremarkable or just okay.  Both of the "on tap" items requested weren't actually available, but what was available was good.

Desserts were delicious.

That being said, sends kid friendly and there was a prom crowd in the place that might have been making things difficult for the staff to handle 

The view really is terrific at night.

Nice assortment of pizza and Italian favorites at reasonable prices.  Waitress was very friendly and attentive.  Rocky's has a traditional dinning area, outside patio, and bar area.  The view of the river from the dinning area and patio is great on nice days.

This place has very good food and their plates are very generous. I had to take half of my lunch for later! The staff is very nice! Great service. It is also a really pretty location near the bridge and the Ohio river.

The view is hard to beat one of the best in Louisville. The service was great. The cheese on the pizza was just melted with few toppings and not much flavor. The beer was flat. I asked for a new pizza and the waiter said it didn't look right and had it remade.

For the last four or five years, every time I have been to Rocky's, I've told myself I'm not coming back.  Service has been poor, food has been poor and the place has looked dingy and not so clean. However, I like to support local businesses and I went 1/29/2018 for lunch.  It was the best experience I've had in ages.  I was seated promptly.  The new GM came to with parm and olive oil and to take my drink order.  My drink order was brought promptly by my server along with a loaf of bread for dipping.  I placed my order.  Food arrived promptly and was tastier than I have received in ages at Rocky's.  As I dined I watched the GM and servers clean tables.  Every item was removed, not just pushed around and tables were given a cleaning.  Everyone was cheerful and I felt as if they were indeed glad to have me their.  Keep up the improvement!!

This review is for a visit in March of 2019. I had the cheese burger with bottomless fries and my wife had a burrito serve queso style. Both the burger and the burrito we're very large portions. Our meal was served hot and the server was very attentive to our needs. Like most Mexican restaurants they will bring you chips and salsa before your meal, it's pretty easy to fill up on these at Tumbleweed.

The food was excellent, the prices were a little higher than expected bcuz we went on a Saturday, so there were no specials, but during weekdays, especially at lunchtime, they offer some good deals. The service was decent, our server wasn't overly friendly, but we got our order & drink refills in a very reasonable amount of time. A good experience all around, would definitely go again, just probably at a time & day of the week when specials are on the menu.

Arrived when they opened and the table was filthy. Queso candle was stuck the table with old, dried queso. Asked that it be cleaned, and heard a staff member say "it's just a film it's not dirty." Lady" films aren't crusty. Server was nice enough, but couldn't remember "two cokes" long enough to ring it in without asking again. And no, they weren't busy. Only one other table occupied at that time. Heard wait staff talking about what colors make hair look punk as they colored on a child's menu. Yeah...
 Probably won't be back. Gone in the toilet.
It was good. The customer service from the manager Stacey Blair was phenomenal. You have a great manager with her.
The food was really good! Service was fast and the waitress even pointed out Facebook specials I was not aware of.
